      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8 Victoria Chambers, ¶ Victoria Street, ¶ Westminster, ¶ s.w ¶ . ¶ 15th December, ¶  ¶ 188 ¶ 3 ¶ Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.12.15<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Robert Smith to James Grant<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Z83/835, unit 1403, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; font-style: italic; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>8 Victoria Chambers,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; font-style: italic; "
               xml:lang="en">Victoria Street,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Westminster,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                    style="font-style: italic; font-variant: small-caps; ">s.w</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15th December,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">188</seg>3</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to enclose copy of a letter which I have received from Mr D. Horowitz,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The enclosed letter was written by D. Horowitz, Forest Conservator, of West Kensington, to J. Cashel Hoey, of the Agent General's Department, London, on 30 November 1882. He wrote saying he had received a request from the Danish Government asking for a report on the 'feasability of rearing Eucalypts in the Danish possessions of the West Indies and which species' he would recommend, and authorising him to buy suitable seeds. He had been unable to buy seeds and so was writing to Hoey to see if he could obtain the following seeds:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>½<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>lb of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">E. globulus</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>¼<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>each of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">E. platyphylla</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">E. obliqua</seg>. He was still collecting information for his report but as the species named 'will grow almost anywhere' wished to at least start with them. The seeds were to be forwarded to the Governor of Santa Cruz, Christiansted, West Indies.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>T. Wilson, Under Secretary, forwarded the correspondence to M on 25 January 1883 'for report as to the best means of obtaining a supply of these seeds.'</p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">Rather than losing this as a Mentions letter, make this a letter dated 25 January 1883, with the location note describing it as a minute on a letter from R, Smith to J, Grant, and then quoting [part of?] the letter in the note.??</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>formerly of the Victorian Forest service, and lately employed by the French Government in planting the Eucalypt in Algeria.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He is desirous of obtaining a small parcel of three kinds of Eucalyptus seed for the Danish Government who wish to try to what extent Eucalypts can be reared in their West Indian Colonies.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have no doubt you will be happy to comply with the wishes of His Danish Majesty's Government, and I would draw to your attention that Mr Horowitz's suggestion as to forwarding it here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honour to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Robt Murray Smith</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honorable</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Chief Secretary,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Eucalyptus</p>
         </div>
